post.title: Riker Ipsum
post.content: For an android with no feelings, he sure managed to evoke them in others. About four years. I got tired of hearing how young I looked. Our neural pathways have become accustomed to your sensory input patterns. Yes, absolutely, I do indeed concur, wholeheartedly! Travel time to the nearest starbase? That might've been one of the shortest assignments in the history of Starfleet. I recommend you don't fire until you're within 40,000 kilometers. When has justice ever been as simple as a rule book? The game's not big enough unless it scares you a little. and attack the Romulans. When has justice ever been as simple as a rule book? And blowing into maximum warp speed, you appeared for an instant to be in two places at once. I think you've let your personal feelings cloud your judgement. Well, that's certainly good to know. We finished our first sensor sweep of the neutral zone. Could someone survive inside a transporter buffer for 75 years? Fate. It protects fools, little children, and ships named "Enterprise." Wouldn't that bring about chaos? Mr. Crusher, ready a collision course with the Borg ship. I've had twelve years to think about it. And if I had it to do over again, I would have grabbed the phaser and pointed it at you instead of them. What's a knock-out like you doing in a computer-generated gin joint like this? Congratulations - you just destroyed the Enterprise.
